TY  - JOUR
AU  - Connor, Gregory
AU  - Korajczyk, Robert A.
T1  - An Intertemporal Equilibrium Beta Pricing Model
PY  - 1989
Y1  - 1989/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/2.3.373
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 2
IS  - 3
SP  - 373
EP  - 392
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article develops an intertemporal, discrete-time, competitive equilibrium version of the arbitrage pricing theory (APT) and explores the econometric implications of this model under various restrictions on investor preferences and on the dynamic behavior of dividends. We describe conditions under which the econometric techniques typically used for estimating and testing the APT can be shown to be consistent with our economic model. We relate our intertemporal version of the APT to the static APT and to Merton’s intertemporal capital asset pricing model.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/2.3.373
ER  - 



