TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bagnoli, Mark
AU  - Gordon, Roger
AU  - Lipman, Barton L.
T1  - Stock Repurchase as a Takeover Defense
PY  - 1989
Y1  - 1989/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/2.3.423
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 2
IS  - 3
SP  - 423
EP  - 443
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We develop a model in which stock repurchases serve as a defense against takeovers by signaling the manager’s private information about the value of the firm. The manager repurchases shares to block a takeover only if the cost of doing so is not too high. Since the cost is inversely related to the value of the firm under his management, a repurchase signals that the value of the stock is high, blocking a takeover. While a repurchase increases the expected value of the stock, it also makes the stock riskier. The model also implies that there are too few takeovers for efficiency.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/2.3.423
ER  - 



